  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening Security and Community Stabilization at the Northern Borders of Cote d&apos;Ivoire</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The key objective of the project, is to enhance security and community stabilization at C&#xF4;te d&#x2019;Ivoire&#x2019;s borders with Mali and Burkina Faso, through activities that bridge the peace and development nexus by improving border management mechanisms, social cohesion and social inclusion, in the context of the COVID-19 pandemic. In order to mitigate increasing violence along at-risk border areas, the intervention will contribute to increasing immigration agents&#x2019; and local authorities capacities to secure safe and orderly cross border mobility (once the closing of borders will be lifted); engaging local populations in border management; ensuring constructive engagement of at-risk youth in the communities; enhancing the participation of women in local conflict management mechanisms; while ensuring overall safe and orderly migration.</narrative>
  </description>
